[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating library dependencies**\n\nI think I need to look into more source configuration, likely without an environment. It might help to check the module docs for getting started with dependencies. It seems like the artifact requires only the scala-library and no extra test dependencies, aside from the Scala compiler due to existing Scala usage. But should I add testImplementation for deterministic setups? I wonder if adding the typed artifact is necessary for meaningful coverage since it might not be required.\n\n**Considering typed actor dependencies**\n\nIt looks like the \"TypedActor\" has been removed along with some old classic typed actors. The issue seems to stem from existing tests referencing the removed API instead of missing dependencies. I need to focus on classic actor APIs found in org.apache.pekko.actor. If I want typed coverage, I might need to use a separate artifact. Also, it appears that certain tests might require the system property --add-exports for proper execution. I wonder if the current setup accounts for this.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0429804a3d107e5d016a406a2f25308193a00b8ddaaa73af00\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQGo6_TpEXhp-pcr6Z6smynSWGW2WHhqTR2EYrMwFaffr0pMMAcZj3Hu_hQf1QFnxb_IaYZKuR3ZBhopqQMq7AxNE9D8pXLRgnDeuye_fvvHHYqcyrA1FoRbCx4qcOcVxr18vUM-g_Nruc7nnlt8UKThjzCzZ29OW_R06I1d6WM1JeMbQ9xYqZPSX7_lgRG0OYnhaEDkI-41O698kvlhIXBqMAxp-6gQtskJ09B_Aifk2SGbYurACJw5flG5Kyy_heHkLa8rtaHI_GK1Jt57AffEBry14UdaW7MAZcRXo2sCZJ2xKeyuSkoizK7cm79wb9yAO8l2iugRyyrbY6rntHRUzEapJGRu4z7jaB1xLIpDvIg-7z0NIC6qP2BfziNDl22RpkyQsQhXXpGL4i-YFUbkUef44RULDBUH4XF-xJyfYhza5tC2KprEjyhGxoo7n_YK3wb2IixiydUaX1qVBCTUI9hBdo4mBwVOC4kawiEiEZSZwAYVEg4T0ul0CuBw0yudOQT8jxFDJ17LkPoaIN2ZVzwb1apO5i9r6RzXTEyyrNwISpHwJbq5HC69LkXPQVAhcsB0H2M1IgQHAIn9puSge2ssROwcKsv4_bO7Vx7hPCe8nF--tnPZJbhExTI9yNT5hfjbwiSg8dwEk1cOgyLn4y6f65Vbc1j