  typed/guide/tutorial_4.html#keeping-track-of-the-device-actors-in-the-group Keeping track of the device actors in the group
  a way to remove device actors from the Map[String, ActorRef[DeviceMessage]]Map<String, ActorRef<DeviceMessage>>. We will assume that when a device is removed, its corresponding device actor is stopped. Supervision, as we discussed earlier, only handles error scenarios — not graceful stopping. So we need to notify the parent when one of the device actors is stopped. Pekko provides a Death Watch feature that allows an actor to watch another actor and be notified if the other actor is stopped. Unlike supervision, watching is not limited to parent-
